OL,4,Cdrivers following coroner's report
OL,6,FDrivers are not subjected to mandatory
OL,7,Fchecks of their skills or health once
OL,8,Fthey obtain their licence, no matter
OL,9,Fhow old they become, although they are
OL,10,Frequired to inform the Driver and
OL,11,FVehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA) if
OL,12,Fthey are no longer fit to drive.
OL,14,FDr Adeley wrote: "Self-reporting of
OL,15,Fvisual conditions permits drivers to
OL,16,Flie about their current driving status
OL,17,Fto those performing an ophthalmic
OL,18,Fassessment and avoid warnings not to
OL,19,Fdrive.
